\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {28}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Genome-wide vulnerability effect summary.} Of 17,453 genes tested, 8,961 (51.3\%) show negative effects (ecDNA$^+$ more dependent). Top 100 candidates show 950$\times $ stronger effects than genome-wide average. No genes pass FDR $<0.05$ after multiple testing correction, reflecting the modest individual effects and limited sample size.}}{22}{table.caption.40}\protected@file@percent }
